{"questionId":"9074175","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A planet is in a circular orbit around a star. The speed of the planet is constant.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the gravitational field of the planet.</p>\n<p>The following data are given:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:180px;\">Mass of planet&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>24</mn></msup></math> kg<br>Radius of the planet&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup></math> m.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>6.4&nbsp;«Nkg<sup>−1</sup> or ms<sup>−2</sup>» ✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074175","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ1.b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the gravitational field of the planet. The following data are given: Mass of planet =8.0×1024 kgRadius of the planet =9.1×106 m.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.2 – Newton’s law of gravitation","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}